{meta: title Candlelight World}
{meta: artist Jean Shepard}
{meta: composer Larry Butler}

{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[C]A checkered cloth red and white
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
And a flickering candlelight
[F]Sets the stage for our story to [G7]unfurl
[C]A lonely girl a handsome man
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
Across the table holding hands
[F]Seeking love in [G7]our candle lighted [C]world
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 4}
Yet the story goes untold
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 5}
For my finger flashes gold
[F]As I reach up to brush a fallen [G7]curl
[C]And your wedding band goes by
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 6}
As you straighten up your tie
[F]Two cheaters in our [G7]candle lighted [C]world
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 7}
[D7]Our unsteady light of love can't
[G7]Hold the darkness back for long
[D7]And the darkness brings a guilty conscience
[G7]When the candle's gone
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 8}
[C]Now my husband back at home
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 9}
And the wife he left alone
[F]Are forgotten as wine and passion [G7]whirl
[C]But who's to take the blame
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 10}
For that solid wall of shame
[F]That borders on our [G7]candle lighted [C]world
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 11}
[F]That borders on our [G7]candle lighted [C]world
{end_of_verse}
